<li id="cite_note-62"><b><a href="#cite_ref-62" title="">^</a></b> "Now, Mr. President, to show you-and it needs but to look at the figures to satisfy the mind of every member-that even a majority of the people within the district of the thirty-nine counties have never come to the polls and expressed their sentiments in favor of a new State. In a voting population of some 40,000 or 50,000 we see a poll of only 17,627-and even some of them were in the [Union] army." Judge Chapman J. Stuart, Wheeling, Dec. 10, 1861, "Debates and Proceedings of the First Constitutional Convention of West Virginia", Vol. 1, pg. 376.</li>
